text: Zhaksylyk Ushkempirov (6 May 1951 - 2 August 2020) was a light-flyweight Greco-Roman wrestler from Kazakhstan. He won an Olympic gold medal in 1980 and a world title in 1981. Ushkempirov took up wrestling in 1969 and won the Soviet title in 1975 and 1980. ==References== Category:1951 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Olympic medalists for Kazakhstan Category:Olympic gold medalists Category:Wrestlers
